sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant User as 👤 User
    participant CLI as 🖥️ main.py CLI
    participant Phases as 📋 lib/phases.py
    participant Orchestrator as ☸️ K8s Orchestrator
    participant K3s as ☁️ K3s Cluster
    participant Job as 📦 K8s Job Pod
    participant Runner as 🤖 Agent Runner<br/>(SDK or CLI)
    participant Claude as 🧠 Claude Agent SDK
    participant Vertex as ☁️ Vertex AI
    participant Jira as 🎫 Jira API
    participant Dashboard as 🎨 Flask Dashboard
    participant Browser as 🌐 Browser

    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
        Note over User,CLI: Phase 1: Initialization
        User->>CLI: python main.py bug-fetch
        CLI->>Jira: Fetch RHOAIENG bugs (REST API)
        Jira-->>CLI: Return bug JSON
        CLI->>CLI: Save to issues/*.json
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note over User,Phases: Phase 2: Pipeline Execution (Local or K8s)
        User->>CLI: python main.py bug-completeness --issue KEY --model opus
        CLI->>Phases: parse_args() → main(args)

        alt Local Execution (default)
            Phases->>Phases: Load skill config (pipeline-skills.yaml)
            Phases->>Phases: Build prompt (templated or native)
            Phases->>Runner: run_agent(prompt, cwd, model, allowed_tools, mcp_servers)

            alt SDK Runner
                Runner->>Claude: ClaudeSDKClient(options).query(prompt)
                Claude->>Vertex: Messages API request
                Vertex-->>Claude: Stream response
                Claude-->>Runner: Response iterator
            else CLI Runner
                Runner->>Runner: subprocess: claude -p "..." --model X --output-format stream-json
                Runner->>Claude: (CLI spawns SDK internally)
                Claude->>Vertex: Messages API request
                Vertex-->>Claude: Stream response
                Claude-->>Runner: Stream-json events via stdout
            end

            Runner-->>Phases: Agent output + success/failure
            Phases->>Phases: Validate JSON schema
            Phases->>Phases: Write workspace/{KEY}/{MODEL}/{phase}.json
            Phases->>Phases: Write workspace/{KEY}/{MODEL}/{phase}.md
            Phases->>Phases: Write logs/{phase}.log
            Phases->>Phases: Broadcast SSE event (if dashboard running)
            Phases-->>CLI: Phase complete
        else K8s Execution (optional)
            Phases->>Orchestrator: submit_phase_job(phase, issue_key, model, runner)
            Orchestrator->>Orchestrator: _create_job_manifest()
            Orchestrator->>K3s: batch_v1.create_namespaced_job()
            K3s->>Job: Schedule pod in ai-pipeline namespace

            Job->>Job: Mount PVCs (issues, workspace, logs, artifacts, context)
            Job->>Job: Load secrets (JIRA_TOKEN, GCP creds, etc.)
            Job->>Job: Init container: update-ca-trust
            Job->>Runner: bash scripts/run_skill.sh or run_skill_sdk.sh

            Runner->>Runner: Load /app/issues/{KEY}.json
            Runner->>Runner: Build prompt from .claude/skills/{skill}/SKILL.md
            Runner->>Claude: ClaudeSDKClient(options).query(prompt) or subprocess
            Claude->>Vertex: Messages API request
            Vertex-->>Claude: Stream response
            Claude-->>Runner: Response

            Runner->>Runner: Write /app/workspace/{KEY}/{MODEL}/{phase}.json
            Runner->>Runner: Write /app/logs/{phase}.log
            Runner->>Runner: Push MLflow trace (optional)
            Runner-->>Job: Exit 0 (success) or 1 (failure)

            Job-->>K3s: Pod completed
            K3s-->>Orchestrator: Job status update
            Orchestrator-->>CLI: get_job_status(job_name)
        end
    end

    rect rgb(230, 255, 230)
        Note over Dashboard,Browser: Phase 3: Monitoring & Visualization
        Browser->>Dashboard: GET / (load dashboard)
        Dashboard->>Dashboard: load_all_issues() → scan issues/*.json
        Dashboard->>Dashboard: load_pipeline_status() → scan workspace/*/*/
        Dashboard->>Dashboard: compute_summary_stats()
        Dashboard-->>Browser: HTML + JavaScript

        Browser->>Dashboard: EventSource /events/stream (SSE)
        Dashboard-->>Browser: SSE: manifest, job_started, job_completed events

        loop Real-time Updates
            Phases->>Dashboard: _broadcast_sse(event)
            Dashboard->>Dashboard: Push to SSE queue
            Dashboard-->>Browser: data: {"event": "job_started", "issue_key": "KEY", ...}
            Browser->>Browser: Update UI table + progress bars
        end

        Browser->>Dashboard: GET /api/issues/{KEY}
        Dashboard->>Dashboard: load_single_issue(KEY) → read workspace files
        Dashboard-->>Browser: JSON with all phase outputs

        Browser->>Dashboard: GET /api/stats
        Dashboard->>Dashboard: compute_all_stats() → aggregate across all issues
        Dashboard-->>Browser: JSON with readiness scores, distributions
    end

    rect rgb(255, 230, 230)
        Note over User,CLI: Phase 4: Validation (optional)
        User->>CLI: python main.py bug-fix-attempt --issue KEY --validation-retries 2
        CLI->>Phases: run_fix_attempt_phase()
        Phases->>Runner: Initial fix attempt
        Runner-->>Phases: patch.diff generated

        Phases->>Phases: is_validation_eligible(component)
        Phases->>Phases: start_validation_container(recipe)
        Phases->>Phases: Podman run -v workspace:/src
        Phases->>Phases: Apply patch + run tests in container

        alt Validation Failed
            Phases->>Phases: Build retry prompt with failure logs
            Phases->>Runner: run_agent(retry_prompt)
            Runner-->>Phases: Updated patch.diff
            Phases->>Phases: Retry validation (up to max retries)
        else Validation Passed
            Phases->>Phases: Mark phase complete
        end

        Phases->>Phases: stop_validation_container()
        Phases-->>CLI: Validation result
    end

    rect rgb(245, 230, 255)
        Note over User,CLI: Phase 5: RFE/Strategy Pipeline (native skills)
        User->>CLI: python main.py rfe-speedrun
        CLI->>Phases: run_rfe_speedrun()
        Phases->>Phases: Resolve remote skill (rfe-creator repo)
        Phases->>Phases: setting_sources=["project"] for skill discovery
        Phases->>Runner: run_agent(cwd=remote_skills/rfe-creator, enable_skills=True)

        Runner->>Claude: Agent has access to sub-skills via Skill tool
        Claude->>Claude: Invoke rfe.create, rfe.review, rfe.split via Skill tool
        Claude-->>Runner: Multi-phase RFE workflow complete

        Runner->>Runner: Write rfes/*.yaml (frontmatter + content)
        Runner-->>Phases: Success
        Phases-->>CLI: RFE pipeline complete
    end

    rect rgb(255, 255, 230)
        Note over User,K3s: Deployment Architecture Notes
        Note over User,K3s: • Vagrant VM: Ubuntu 24.04, 8GB RAM, 8 CPU, 100GB disk<br/>• K3s: Lightweight Kubernetes (single-node)<br/>• Storage: 5x PVCs for issues, workspace, logs, artifacts, context<br/>• Secrets: JIRA_TOKEN, GCP service account, MCP URLs<br/>• Services: Dashboard (Flask), MLflow, Jira/GitHub emulators<br/>• Jobs: Dynamic K8s Jobs for parallel agent execution<br/>• Networking: NFS mount from host → VM, port forwards for dashboard
    end
